8.18.19  10:38 pm   8.17.19  10:24 pm i don't know what exactly you're trying to do so this may not be helpful at all but things stop moving (at least on my laptop) when I scroll up past the newest entry? there's no way to stop new things from being added but scrolling up stops things from moving while you're trying to read them or whatever.

      as for hiding processes you can either control + click on a process and it comes up a menu option to "hide process x" or if you know what the process is called you can go into the search bar, type the process you're trying to hide and hit enter, then click the little "any" next to it and then choose "process" and "does not contain" and you can also save the search so you don't have to keep doing this every time, webkit i'm pretty sure is called com.apple.WebKit.WebContent

8.18.19  9:29 pm   8.17.19  10:24 pm i have access to a bunch of mac laptops from various (2009-2019) years tomorrow, i will attempt to do some experimenting then. your first issue seems to be a glitch, but as to the second: have you tried following the directions on this page?

https://support.apple.com/guide/console/find-log-messages-and-activities-cnslbf30b61a/1.1/mac/10.14

from what i understand, you first create a filter by right clicking to show or hide a process; the filter moves to the search menu. then, you click the arrow that appears next to the filter, which opens up a host of options to do things like "hide anything that contains xyz" or "hide any process of specific types".

the pictures given by this page seem to indicate that this can be inclusive or exclusive, depending on whether the filter is blue or red. i don't know if you have the right kind of mac to use this fu nctional ity though

8.18.19  5:57 pm   Do you think that it's possible to force yourself to be smart/intelligent?
I just don't think I've ever been smart.. Sure, I had all A's in school when I was younger, but that was due to my extreme perfectionism. at the time i thought that if i ever were to get a grade lower than A, i'd instantly fail in life and die.
People who are naturally intelligent remain being intelligent until they die. I was a "smart" kid back then, but now I'm average at best when it comes to intelligence. Some of my good friends even consider me extremely dumb. Am I just going through a "dumb" phase right now or have I always been dumb? I'm not sure..
